-- U.K. Pound Weakens Through $1.50 for First Time Since July 2010
-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2013-03-01T14:22:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-01/u-k-pound-weakens-through-1-50-for-first-time-since-july-2010.html
The pound extended its decline
against the dollar, weakening through $1.50 for the first time
since July 13, 2010.  The British currency dropped as much as 1.1 percent to
$1.4999 and was at $1.5013 as of 2:22 p.m. London time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
